  "body": "Hi, @haltman-at, @gnidan\r\n### Issue\r\n\r\n   1 vulnerability (high severity) is introduced in **_@truffle/contract-schema_**:\r\n   Vulnerability **SNYK-JS-CRYPTOJS-548472** (high severity) is detected in package **_crypto-js_** (versions: <3.2.1,>=3.3.0 <4.0.0):  [ https://snyk.io/vuln/SNYK-JS-CRYPTOJS-548472]( https://snyk.io/vuln/SNYK-JS-CRYPTOJS-548472)\r\n  The above vulnerable package is referenced by **_@truffle/contract-schema_** via:\r\n` @truffle/contract-schema@3.4.1 ➔ crypto-js@3.3.0`\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\nSince **_@truffle/contract-schema 3.4.*_** is transitively referenced by **276** downstream projects (e.g., [@truffle/contract 4.3.19](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@truffle/contract) (latest version), [@chainlink/contracts 0.1.7](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@chainlink/contracts) (latest version), [truffle-contract 4.0.31](https://www.npmjs.com/package/truffle-contract)  (latest version), [@openzeppelin/test-helpers 0.5.11](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@openzeppelin/test-helpers) (latest version), [@nomiclabs/truffle-contract 4.2.23](https://www.npmjs.com/package/@nomiclabs/truffle-contract) (latest version)), \r\n\r\nIf **_@truffle/contract-schema_** removes the vulnerable packages from the above versions, then its fixed version can help downstream users decrease their pain.\r\n\r\nCould you help update packages in 3.4.*?\r\n\r\n### Fixing suggestions\r\n\r\nIn **_@truffle/contract-schema 3.4.*_**, you can kindly perform the following upgrades :\r\n`crypto-js ^3.1.9-1 ➔  ~3.2.1`;  \r\n\r\n**Note:**\r\n_>crypto-js@3.2.1，<3.3.0 have fixed the vulnerability SNYK-JS-CRYPTOJS-548472_\r\n\r\n\r\nThanks for your contributions to the npm ecosystem!\r\n\r\nBest regards,\r\nPaimon",
